  "chapter": {
    "number": 6,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Paul’s Hardships and God’s Grace"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "As God’s fellow workers,",
          {
            "noteId": 820
          },
          "then, we urge you not to receive God’s grace in vain."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "For He says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“In the time of favor I heard you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in the day of salvation I helped you.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 821
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "Behold, now is the time of favor; now is the day of salvation!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "We put no obstacle in anyone’s way, so that no one can discredit our ministry."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Rather, as servants of God we commend ourselves in every way: in great endurance; in troubles, hardships, and calamities;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "in beatings, imprisonments, and riots; in labor, sleepless nights, and hunger;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "in purity, knowledge, patience, and kindness; in the Holy Spirit and in sincere love;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "in truthful speech and in the power of God; with the weapons of righteousness in the right hand and in the left;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "through glory and dishonor, slander and praise; viewed as imposters, yet genuine;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "as unknown, yet well-known; dying, and yet we live on; punished, yet not killed;"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; poor, yet making many rich; having nothing, and yet possessing everything."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "We have spoken freely to you, Corinthians. Our hearts are open wide."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "It is not our affection, but yours, that is restrained."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "As a fair exchange, I ask you as my children: Open wide your hearts also."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Do Not Be Unequally Yoked"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "Do not be unequally yoked with unbelievers. For what partnership can righteousness have with wickedness? Or what fellowship does light have with darkness?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "What harmony is there between Christ and Belial?",
          {
            "noteId": 822
          },
          "Or what does a believer have in common with an unbeliever?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "What agreement can exist between the temple of God and idols? For we are the temple of the living God. As God has said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will dwell with them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and walk among them,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will be their God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will be My people.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 823
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Therefore come out from among them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and be separate, says the Lord.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Touch no unclean thing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will receive you.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 824
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "And:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will be a Father to you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will be My sons and daughters,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "says the Lord Almighty.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 825
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
